File: Dischem JOHANNESBURG - Pharmacy and beauty retailer Dis-Chem is the latest company to launch a one-hour delivery service. The company's DeliverD service will be integrated into the company's existing mobile app. During the trial phase, Dis-chem says it will launch a limited assortment of front-shop products. READ: Dis-Chem ready to administer vaccines And thereafter, customers will be able to shop 7,000 items across store departments. The delivery service will be tested in selected stores across Johannesburg and other major metropolitan areas before being extended to other regions.